WEBVTT

00:09.792 --> 00:12.882
[♪♪]

01:01.148 --> 01:04.194
[suspenseful music]

01:29.828 --> 01:32.918
[birds chirping]

02:01.295 --> 02:04.385
[suspenseful music]

02:27.495 --> 02:29.149
[loud thud]

02:35.633 --> 02:39.246
[mysterious music]

03:13.062 --> 03:16.196
[Betriek humming]

03:24.204 --> 03:27.207
-[speaking Dutch]

03:30.079 --> 03:32.168
[rat squeaking]

03:44.311 --> 03:47.357
[loud thumps]

03:56.627 --> 03:59.935
[woman screaming]

04:03.417 --> 04:06.855
[screaming continues]

04:06.898 --> 04:09.553
[rat squeaking]

04:14.079 --> 04:17.126
[suspenseful music]

04:28.529 --> 04:31.923
[loud clatter]

04:36.841 --> 04:39.453
[dramatic music]

04:53.597 --> 04:55.599
[phone vibrating]

05:03.651 --> 05:05.609
-[speaking Dutch]

05:05.740 --> 05:07.785
-[speaking Dutch]

05:13.530 --> 05:16.968
[phone ringing]

05:19.884 --> 05:21.495
-[speaking Dutch]

05:31.809 --> 05:32.984
[horn honking]

05:35.552 --> 05:37.641
-[Hanna laughs]
-[chuckles]

05:37.685 --> 05:39.817
[phone beeps]

05:39.861 --> 05:41.166
[exhales deeply]

05:42.472 --> 05:45.562
[♪♪]

06:42.010 --> 06:43.577
[door opens]

06:51.541 --> 06:52.890
-Oh?

07:31.276 --> 07:33.714
[knock on door]
[Roelof] [speaking Dutch] Yeah?

07:35.280 --> 07:36.673
-Oh.

07:49.338 --> 07:51.253
[door closes with a creak]

08:06.616 --> 08:07.965
-Oh.

08:14.711 --> 08:16.278
-Hm.

08:29.160 --> 08:30.727
-Mmmm.

08:33.991 --> 08:35.471
-[grunts]

08:35.515 --> 08:37.517
-[laughs]

08:37.560 --> 08:39.170
-[laughs]

08:42.391 --> 08:44.349
[mellow music]

08:46.569 --> 08:49.572
[bird calling]

09:01.889 --> 09:05.849
[spade hitting ground]

09:50.764 --> 09:54.332
[suspenseful music]

10:07.563 --> 10:10.392
[dramatic music]

10:18.095 --> 10:21.185
[somber music]

10:23.057 --> 10:25.059
-[speaking Dutch]

10:26.756 --> 10:29.193
-[indistinct conversations]

10:29.237 --> 10:34.503
[♪♪]

10:52.739 --> 10:54.305
-Hallo, hallo, hallo, hallo.

11:06.143 --> 11:09.233
[♪♪]

11:09.625 --> 11:11.671
-[Sonja]
Really glad you could come

11:11.714 --> 11:13.368
on such short notice,
by the way.

11:13.411 --> 11:15.370
-No problem.
I'm excited to see it.

11:15.413 --> 11:17.024
-Yeah.

11:17.067 --> 11:19.809
So, we don't know how long
she's been exposed

11:19.853 --> 11:21.985
to the outside air--
-Okay.

11:22.029 --> 11:26.294
-But locals found her
about four days ago.

11:26.337 --> 11:29.645
They thought it was recent
'cause it's so well preserved.

11:29.689 --> 11:32.300
Oh, watch your step here.

11:32.343 --> 11:33.693
Oh, I believe
you know Lennard.

11:33.736 --> 11:35.564
-Hi, Lennard.
Good to see you again.

11:35.607 --> 11:38.132
-Good to see you.
-Is Radu around?

11:38.175 --> 11:40.177
-Yeah, he's around somewhere.
-Good.

11:40.221 --> 11:41.439
-I can't say
what an honor it is--

11:41.483 --> 11:43.528
-What is going on with that?

11:43.572 --> 11:45.313
I saw it on the way in.

11:45.356 --> 11:48.229
[Sonja] Unfortunately, they
found the man who was digging

11:48.272 --> 11:50.535
in his own pit this morning.

11:50.579 --> 11:52.015
-Dead?
-[Sonja] Hm-mm.

11:52.059 --> 11:54.539
Yeah, they say he died
of hypothermia.

11:54.583 --> 11:57.629
A heart attack,
resulting from hypothermia.

11:57.673 --> 11:58.935
[Jonas]
That's terrible.

11:58.979 --> 12:02.199
And the pit?

12:02.243 --> 12:04.419
-Well, we're not allowed
to check it out yet.

12:05.550 --> 12:06.943
-Oh, of course.

12:08.902 --> 12:10.947
-Shall we?

12:10.991 --> 12:12.906
So, we've tried to protect
the site from the elements

12:12.949 --> 12:14.995
as well as we could.

12:15.038 --> 12:16.300
I hope it's satisfactory.

12:16.344 --> 12:18.520
-Yeah, okay.

12:19.477 --> 12:20.565
Okay.

12:21.828 --> 12:23.046
Sorry.

12:25.309 --> 12:26.441
Sorry.

12:33.230 --> 12:35.232
That is incredible.

12:39.193 --> 12:42.152
[♪♪]

12:45.939 --> 12:47.331
Look at that.

12:52.423 --> 12:54.077
Isn't she beautiful?

12:55.818 --> 12:58.952
[mysterious music]

12:58.995 --> 13:00.301
-[gasps]

13:02.303 --> 13:05.262
[breathes heavily]

13:05.306 --> 13:08.570
[loud regular thumps]

13:11.529 --> 13:13.096
Mum. Hey!

13:13.140 --> 13:14.358
Mum.

13:15.707 --> 13:16.883
Hey.

13:42.386 --> 13:43.648
[Betriek gasps]

13:52.353 --> 13:55.399
[♪♪]

14:09.065 --> 14:10.110
-Nee.

14:14.070 --> 14:15.724
-[exhales]

14:24.907 --> 14:26.778
[Betriek gasps]

14:56.983 --> 15:00.073
[♪♪]

15:07.732 --> 15:09.909
[Hanna] Mama.

15:12.781 --> 15:15.653
Mama.

15:15.697 --> 15:18.004
Mama.

15:25.620 --> 15:27.317
Wat?

15:27.361 --> 15:31.669
[muted chatter]

15:41.331 --> 15:42.593
-Sir, can I help you?

15:44.117 --> 15:46.249
Yes, yes.

15:50.993 --> 15:52.995
-We had someone walking around
the house

15:53.039 --> 15:55.215
this morning.
-One of ours?

16:03.963 --> 16:05.790
-What he's trying to say is that

16:05.834 --> 16:08.663
[clears throat] the next time
something like this happens,

16:08.706 --> 16:12.188
this person will probably not
receive a very warm welcome.

16:13.320 --> 16:16.366
-Ah, okay.
So that's what he's saying?

16:17.150 --> 16:19.195
-Something like that.

16:21.719 --> 16:22.982
-Mooi.

16:24.853 --> 16:27.203
[Jonas] So...listen.

16:27.247 --> 16:29.205
I'm sorry that this happened.

16:29.249 --> 16:31.120
I will make sure to tell my crew

16:31.164 --> 16:34.384
not to go exploring
on their own. Okay?

16:34.428 --> 16:36.517
-Are you guys
digging for treasure?

16:40.651 --> 16:42.262
-Yeah. Something like that.

17:30.571 --> 17:31.746
-Ja.

17:57.859 --> 17:59.208
[clicks]

18:19.968 --> 18:23.014
[plaintive violin notes]

18:40.293 --> 18:41.511
[knock on door]

18:45.080 --> 18:46.429
-Ja?

18:46.473 --> 18:48.692
[door opens]

19:11.802 --> 19:13.369
[sighs]

19:15.458 --> 19:19.201
[muted chatter]

19:19.245 --> 19:21.116
[Jonas] Okay.
I have another one.

19:21.160 --> 19:22.813
When, after the plane is landed,

19:22.857 --> 19:24.424
and people jump out
of their seats,

19:24.467 --> 19:26.295
grabbing their luggage,

19:26.339 --> 19:28.819
like they're
in a terrible hurry.

19:28.863 --> 19:31.213
But then, of course,
the doors don't open

19:31.257 --> 19:33.041
until 15 minutes later.

19:33.084 --> 19:34.303
And they all stand there,

19:34.347 --> 19:36.131
just cramped together
in the aisle

19:36.175 --> 19:38.089
like a bunch of idiots.

19:38.133 --> 19:41.180
I fucking hate that.
-[laughs]

19:41.223 --> 19:44.226
That's a good one.
Yeah, that's a good one.

19:45.358 --> 19:46.315
-Thanks.

19:46.359 --> 19:48.796
-No worries.
-[laughs]

19:51.886 --> 19:53.801
-Shouldn't you join them again?

19:55.063 --> 19:57.674
-Nah, we're doing fine.

19:57.718 --> 20:02.288
I could just sit here
and exude authority.

20:03.376 --> 20:04.855
-Okay.
-Yeah.

20:04.899 --> 20:06.509
-Yeah.

20:06.553 --> 20:08.685
Oh, what about people
who take everything

20:08.729 --> 20:10.513
that's even remotely
considered free?

20:10.557 --> 20:12.211
-Okay.

20:12.254 --> 20:16.215
-You know, like, um...
ah, like those bags of sugar.

20:16.258 --> 20:20.175
They-they don't need them,
but they take them anyway.

20:20.219 --> 20:22.873
-[laughs]
Is this about your mother again?

20:22.917 --> 20:24.832
-Oh, my God.
She is terrible!

20:24.875 --> 20:27.661
She collects those things
like a hamster.

20:27.704 --> 20:29.880
Yeah, and when we have guests,
she presents them

20:29.924 --> 20:32.231
with this whole array
of sugar bags

20:32.274 --> 20:33.884
which she stole.

20:33.928 --> 20:35.669
-[laughs]

20:35.712 --> 20:36.974
Wow.

20:37.018 --> 20:39.629
-Yeah, she gets under my skin.
-Uh-huh.

20:42.458 --> 20:47.376
-As your local guide,
I would advise you to try the...

20:47.420 --> 20:51.380
Witte Koppenjenever next.
It's absolutely delicious.

20:51.424 --> 20:54.296
-Oh, um, I'm pretty sure
I had several of those already

20:54.340 --> 20:58.822
and I'm not sure that I can
sit here and exude authority...

21:02.435 --> 21:05.829
I think I'm getting
a bit too relaxed...

21:07.266 --> 21:10.051
[Betriek] Men who keep
their socks on in bed.

21:10.094 --> 21:12.575
-Socks, yeah.
Bloody philistines.

21:15.709 --> 21:19.016
You know what?
I think I have to call it a day.

21:19.060 --> 21:20.279
-Are you okay?

21:20.322 --> 21:23.325
-[gagging, coughs]

21:24.935 --> 21:26.937
Ah, for helvede!

21:26.981 --> 21:28.330
What have you done to me?

21:29.549 --> 21:31.768
-Don't fight it.

21:34.815 --> 21:36.207
Lovely.

21:37.557 --> 21:41.256
Yeah, we would just drive
and play gigs everywhere.

21:41.300 --> 21:45.521
Sometimes for like five people,
but that was fine too, you know?

21:46.653 --> 21:48.785
[Jonas] Does your daughter
remember it?

21:49.612 --> 21:53.094
[Betriek]
No, but she likes his voice.

21:55.009 --> 21:57.794
I played her some songs
of us in the car.

21:57.838 --> 22:00.362
He had a very beautiful
singing voice.

22:01.668 --> 22:03.191
So does she, actually.

22:04.105 --> 22:06.890
-No chest pains,
no fatigue, no nothing?

22:06.934 --> 22:08.152
-No.

22:08.196 --> 22:10.633
-His heart just said fuck it.

22:10.677 --> 22:13.419
No more oxygen for this asshole.

22:15.029 --> 22:16.987
[inhales deeply]

22:17.031 --> 22:18.728
How's the head?

22:20.164 --> 22:22.645
-Trying to avoid
sudden movements.

22:22.689 --> 22:25.387
[laughs]

22:25.431 --> 22:28.651
You know, I am usually better
at handling hard liquor.

22:28.695 --> 22:29.826
-[Betriek] Yeah.
-I'm Danish and all.

22:29.870 --> 22:31.654
-Of course.
Of course.

22:34.048 --> 22:35.354
-[laughs]

22:38.574 --> 22:42.056
There must be like
a million guys out there

22:42.099 --> 22:44.363
waiting for a chance
to make you happy.

22:44.406 --> 22:46.190
-[laughs]

22:46.234 --> 22:48.497
Well, I'm sorry to inform you
that I'm not really considered

22:48.541 --> 22:50.020
relationship material
around here.

22:50.064 --> 22:51.152
-Come on.

22:51.195 --> 22:52.632
-No, seriously.

22:54.242 --> 22:55.330
They're all afraid.

22:56.897 --> 22:58.072
Family curse.

22:58.115 --> 23:00.901
-[scoffs] Family curse?
-Yeah.

23:00.944 --> 23:03.164
-'Cause your husband died?

23:03.207 --> 23:07.168
-Yeah, that...
and some other stuff.

23:07.211 --> 23:09.170
It's a boring story.

23:09.213 --> 23:10.389
-Nutshell.

23:15.524 --> 23:17.700
-Well, my grandmother
was murdered when I was a kid

23:17.744 --> 23:19.310
and they never found out
who did it.

23:19.354 --> 23:20.703
[Jonas] Wow.

23:20.747 --> 23:22.792
-My dad went a bit crazy
after that,

23:22.836 --> 23:24.925
started drinking, lost his job.

23:24.968 --> 23:27.536
My mum became
emotionally unavailable.

23:28.972 --> 23:31.540
And nowadays, she's suffering
from this mysterious illness

23:31.584 --> 23:33.803
nobody really seems to know
how to deal with.

23:35.979 --> 23:38.242
I escaped it all for a while
when I went to New York.

23:38.286 --> 23:40.201
But then Neil died,

23:40.244 --> 23:43.073
leaving me with this little
firecracker called Hanna.

23:44.901 --> 23:47.164
-Jesus.

23:47.208 --> 23:50.341
That sounds
like a...a proper curse.

23:53.083 --> 23:55.346
-Yeah. Doesn't it?

23:58.698 --> 24:00.134
-This is me.

24:04.617 --> 24:07.010
Well, thank you
for telling me all of this

24:07.054 --> 24:09.012
before we spend
a whole evening together.

24:09.056 --> 24:11.798
-[chuckles] Well, usually,
it takes a little bit longer

24:11.841 --> 24:16.106
for disaster to strike, so...
I'll stay out of your way.

24:17.020 --> 24:18.108
-Yes, please.

24:19.458 --> 24:21.024
-I'll see you around.

24:30.599 --> 24:33.210
[loud boisterous chatter]

24:40.696 --> 24:43.786
[children singing]

24:48.138 --> 24:50.097
[speaking Dutch]

24:50.140 --> 24:52.708
[children singing]

25:05.286 --> 25:08.376
[soft music]

25:19.605 --> 25:22.608
-[speaking Dutch]

25:23.565 --> 25:24.610
-Ja?

26:15.312 --> 26:16.400
-Oké.

26:17.314 --> 26:19.839
[receding footsteps]

26:21.928 --> 26:24.757
[♪♪]

26:26.323 --> 26:29.588
[♪♪]

26:35.594 --> 26:36.986
-Mama!

26:38.727 --> 26:41.556
[♪♪]

26:54.308 --> 26:57.354
[soft whispering]

27:08.714 --> 27:10.106
-Oké.

27:13.240 --> 27:15.721
-Mama?
-Uh-huh.

27:36.916 --> 27:38.569
-[chuckles]

27:40.310 --> 27:43.400
[crickets chirping]

28:03.116 --> 28:04.204
-Ja.

28:09.209 --> 28:12.125
[bird calling]

28:12.168 --> 28:14.170
[exhales]

28:17.217 --> 28:18.740
Wel...

28:25.051 --> 28:26.226
[sniffles]

28:30.534 --> 28:31.753
[sighs]

28:32.711 --> 28:33.886
[door creaks open]

28:35.888 --> 28:37.759
[door creaks closed]

29:01.827 --> 29:03.393
[gasps]

29:03.437 --> 29:06.309
[♪♪]

29:08.572 --> 29:09.965
-I'm sorry.

29:12.011 --> 29:13.752
I'm sorry.

29:15.536 --> 29:18.191
I took some of your milk.

29:21.281 --> 29:24.501
[suspenseful music]

29:24.545 --> 29:25.981
-That's okay.

29:28.941 --> 29:31.944
-[breathes shakily]

29:31.987 --> 29:33.467
-Just, uh...

29:35.295 --> 29:38.167
Just wait here. Okay?

29:38.211 --> 29:39.299
-Please.

29:41.344 --> 29:42.563
Please.

29:43.564 --> 29:46.654
[suspenseful music]

29:56.882 --> 29:58.013
[gasps]

29:59.406 --> 30:01.277
-I'm sorry.

30:01.321 --> 30:03.714
I'm sorry.

30:05.281 --> 30:06.935
[man]
They're making me do it.

30:11.984 --> 30:14.638
[♪♪]

30:14.682 --> 30:15.770
[Elske screams]

30:22.559 --> 30:24.344
[Betriek grunts]

30:24.387 --> 30:27.216
[singing in foreign language]

30:32.918 --> 30:33.875
[Betriek screams]

30:33.919 --> 30:35.398
[glass shatters]

30:37.923 --> 30:40.534
[screams]

30:45.191 --> 30:48.759
[loud screaming]

31:04.688 --> 31:06.429
-Go away.

31:07.778 --> 31:09.084
Please.

31:14.263 --> 31:16.875
[groans]

31:24.883 --> 31:27.755
[tense music]

31:35.241 --> 31:37.460
-[loud thud]
-[Elske groans]

31:37.504 --> 31:38.722
-Mama!

31:42.248 --> 31:43.292
-[thud]
-[grunts]

31:50.734 --> 31:51.822
[Hanny crying]

31:57.611 --> 31:59.178
-[sobbing]

31:59.221 --> 32:02.311
[♪♪]

32:55.147 --> 32:56.235
[Betriek]
Hi.

32:57.976 --> 32:59.020
-Hi.

33:10.814 --> 33:13.121
Again, I'm so sorry
to hear what happened.

33:13.165 --> 33:14.731
It's unbelievable.

33:15.994 --> 33:19.519
Known the guy for ages.
He wouldn't hurt a fly.

33:19.562 --> 33:21.086
The whole crew liked him.

33:21.129 --> 33:22.826
I don't know what could've
gotten into him.

33:25.786 --> 33:28.223
-[speaking Dutch]

33:41.149 --> 33:43.064
-They understand.

33:43.108 --> 33:45.240
It's not your fault.
You couldn't have known.

33:49.244 --> 33:55.642
This man, I'd say he's
no older than 40, 45 maybe.

33:56.599 --> 33:57.948
-Yeah.

33:57.992 --> 34:03.041
-So, in 1991...

34:04.303 --> 34:09.047
...he would have been 10, 15.

34:10.657 --> 34:11.745
-Yeah.

34:13.268 --> 34:15.270
And living in Romania.

34:19.492 --> 34:22.451
-[sucking pacifier]

34:26.238 --> 34:27.413
-Can we talk?

34:28.631 --> 34:29.850
Upstairs?

34:34.768 --> 34:36.509
Boy, you're pretty brave
coming here.

34:38.859 --> 34:41.209
See how we're super cursed?

34:43.124 --> 34:44.517
It's pretty obvious, huh?

34:52.264 --> 34:54.918
[sobbing]

34:54.962 --> 34:56.311
-Hey. Hey.

34:58.183 --> 35:01.142
-[sobbing continues]

35:07.496 --> 35:08.628
-Come here.

35:10.673 --> 35:14.068
[sobbing]

35:41.704 --> 35:43.097
[clatter]

35:57.155 --> 35:59.157
[loud clatter]

36:00.680 --> 36:03.596
[♪♪]

36:09.341 --> 36:11.038
[keypad clicking]

36:13.562 --> 36:16.217
[machine beeps]

36:16.261 --> 36:19.046
-[speaking Dutch]
-[speaking Dutch]

36:19.177 --> 36:21.396
[keypad clicking, machine beeps]

36:22.789 --> 36:24.182
[Elske exhales]

36:33.626 --> 36:35.280
[horn honks]

36:52.079 --> 36:55.125
[suspenseful music]

37:16.930 --> 37:19.498
[machine beeping]

37:45.567 --> 37:48.657
[suspenseful music]

38:03.193 --> 38:06.501
[suspenseful music]

39:05.299 --> 39:08.737
[static charge breakdown]

39:12.524 --> 39:16.354
-[eerie whispering]

39:28.191 --> 39:29.236
[gasps]

39:32.413 --> 39:35.677
[heavy breathing]

39:38.288 --> 39:41.379
[suspenseful music]

39:43.076 --> 39:45.295
[breathes heavily]

39:45.339 --> 39:49.038
[suspenseful music]

39:50.344 --> 39:52.955
[girl screams]

39:52.999 --> 39:54.392
[creaking]

39:58.047 --> 40:00.615
[elevator bell dings]
[crying]

40:17.719 --> 40:19.721
[sighs]

40:21.593 --> 40:23.421
Hey.

40:33.082 --> 40:34.997
[muted chatter]

40:39.741 --> 40:40.829
Hey.

40:42.396 --> 40:43.441
Hey.

40:48.097 --> 40:49.447
[Betriek]
Hey.

40:49.490 --> 40:50.491
-Just a minute.

40:51.492 --> 40:52.493
-Hey.

40:52.537 --> 40:54.321
-I'm here with my mum.

40:54.364 --> 40:56.671
-Okay.
-You are going to see that man.

40:57.977 --> 40:59.500
-Uh, Radu?

40:59.544 --> 41:01.241
-Hmm.
-Yeah.

41:01.284 --> 41:03.765
-Did they say anything about
why he could have done it?

41:03.809 --> 41:06.333
-No. Well, he hasn't
woken up yet, so...

41:09.815 --> 41:11.773
At camp, they were saying, uh...
-[Elske] Betriek!

41:13.296 --> 41:14.384
-What?

41:16.169 --> 41:19.477
-Um, they were saying
that he was digging.

41:19.520 --> 41:20.782
-Digging?

41:20.826 --> 41:24.307
-On his own.
Away from the site.

41:24.351 --> 41:26.832
Such a strange
coincidence, right?

41:28.442 --> 41:29.661
[Elske]
Betriek!

41:31.663 --> 41:33.099
-What are you doing tomorrow?

41:34.100 --> 41:37.973
[lively chatter]

41:44.937 --> 41:48.549
Hey, right on time.

41:49.202 --> 41:50.812
-Not this place again.

41:50.856 --> 41:52.031
-Bad memories?

41:55.251 --> 41:58.341
Do you see the old man
sitting over there?

41:58.385 --> 42:00.039
-Who?
-Him.

42:02.911 --> 42:05.958
His son was the guy who died
in the bar a couple of days ago.

42:06.001 --> 42:08.308
Just after he dug something up.

42:11.398 --> 42:12.486
What was it?

42:16.882 --> 42:17.926
What was it?

42:24.411 --> 42:25.499
-A woman.

42:26.892 --> 42:28.850
-A woman?
-No, sorry.

42:28.894 --> 42:32.593
A very old--
very old woman.

42:32.637 --> 42:35.335
Hundreds of years.
A bog body.

42:36.597 --> 42:38.381
-How old, exactly?

42:38.425 --> 42:42.298
-We're still running tests.
But old.

42:44.431 --> 42:45.563
What?

42:46.694 --> 42:47.782
-Come.

42:49.567 --> 42:52.047
[Jonas] I'm not sure
that I understand correctly.

42:52.091 --> 42:54.310
But are you saying that
your son knew where to dig

42:54.354 --> 42:55.921
to find this woman?

42:55.964 --> 42:57.792
[Ton] Cheers.
-Cheers

42:59.664 --> 43:02.231
-We are a very sensitive family.

43:02.275 --> 43:05.626
My father, me,
but especially Micha.

43:05.670 --> 43:08.629
He always know things.
-[phone vibrates]

43:08.673 --> 43:10.588
[speaking Dutch]

43:16.376 --> 43:22.077
-So, could it be that
it was whispered to him?

43:22.121 --> 43:23.731
Where to dig?

43:24.819 --> 43:25.907
-Eh...

43:34.916 --> 43:36.614
Helen's whispers.

43:39.007 --> 43:41.357
She talks about this.

43:41.401 --> 43:44.709
The legend...of Feike.

43:45.535 --> 43:47.320
Yeah.

44:17.567 --> 44:19.134
Excuse me.

44:20.527 --> 44:21.920
-What's going on?

44:23.965 --> 44:26.968
-Uh, s-sorry.
[sniffles]

44:45.508 --> 44:48.686
[♪♪]

45:01.046 --> 45:02.177
[Jonas]
So, who's Helen?

45:03.135 --> 45:05.615
-[scoffs] I can't believe
you don't know.

45:05.659 --> 45:06.704
-What?

45:07.661 --> 45:13.362
-You science boys,
you're uninformed.

45:13.406 --> 45:14.973
[laughs]
-Come on.

45:16.017 --> 45:18.803
-He's sort of the villain
in this whole legend of Feike,

45:18.846 --> 45:22.458
like there's something evil
out there in the bog,

45:22.502 --> 45:25.592
whispering horrible things
to anyone who listens.

45:25.635 --> 45:27.376
[chuckles]

45:27.420 --> 45:29.204
It's a stupid story...
[clears throat]

45:29.248 --> 45:32.207
...just to scare kids
away from the bog.

45:32.251 --> 45:33.731
-Like a boogie man?

45:33.774 --> 45:34.819
-Yeah.

45:36.821 --> 45:39.388
Some people take it
pretty seriously, though.

45:39.432 --> 45:40.738
You'll see.

45:42.609 --> 45:45.133
Oh, we have our annual
celebration in a few days

45:45.177 --> 45:50.443
and it's...including the school
musical, it's ridiculous.

45:50.486 --> 45:51.923
-And do you?

45:51.966 --> 45:53.011
-What?
-Take it seriously.

45:53.054 --> 45:54.142
-No.

45:58.581 --> 45:59.931
I hate the story.

46:04.805 --> 46:06.894
My dad said he heard it once.

46:08.983 --> 46:10.245
The whispers.

46:10.289 --> 46:13.074
[Jonas laughs]

46:13.118 --> 46:14.989
[Betriek] Actually,
I think I heard it, too.

46:16.643 --> 46:18.819
In the hospital.

46:18.863 --> 46:21.517
What?

46:21.561 --> 46:23.302
-What do you want me to say?

46:23.345 --> 46:24.651
I mean, come on.

46:26.131 --> 46:27.175
-Nothing.

46:29.438 --> 46:30.700
Just say nothing.

46:38.491 --> 46:40.623
Just tell me about this woman
you guys are digging up.

46:40.667 --> 46:42.756
I want to know.
[Jonas] No.

46:42.800 --> 46:44.192
I'm not gonna tell you anything

46:44.236 --> 46:45.933
if it makes you
all paranoid and weird.

46:45.977 --> 46:48.283
-What-- Sorry, paranoid?

46:48.327 --> 46:49.719
-Yeah.

46:49.763 --> 46:52.331
-A guy came into my house,
where I live,

46:52.374 --> 46:54.115
where my family lives.

46:54.159 --> 46:56.465
He tried to kill us, and then
he got his brains bashed in,

46:56.509 --> 46:57.989
in front of me.
-I know.

46:58.032 --> 46:59.555
-Yeah, so don't--

46:59.599 --> 47:00.730
-Don't what?

47:01.819 --> 47:03.124
-Don't treat me like a nutcase.

47:03.168 --> 47:05.779
-That's not what I'm doing.

47:08.695 --> 47:10.349
You're traumatized,
and it may have altered

47:10.392 --> 47:12.786
your perception of things,
that's all I'm saying.

47:12.830 --> 47:14.483
-Fuck you.
-What do you mean, fuck you?

47:14.527 --> 47:16.529
-Fuck-- Fuck you.

47:16.572 --> 47:19.184
Stop the car.
Stop the fucking car!

47:19.227 --> 47:21.316
-Betriek.
-[tires screeching]

47:25.755 --> 47:26.844
[Jonas]
Betriek!

47:28.671 --> 47:31.022
Where are you going?

47:31.065 --> 47:32.675
[Jonas mumbling]

47:34.808 --> 47:36.027
Betriek.

47:37.855 --> 47:39.247
Betriek!
-No!

47:41.206 --> 47:42.685
-[speaking Danish]

47:44.078 --> 47:45.601
We need to go back to the camp.

47:45.645 --> 47:46.907
-Yeah, fuck off!

47:48.039 --> 47:50.041
[Jonas]
You're drunk!

47:50.084 --> 47:52.173
I didn't mean it that way.

47:52.217 --> 47:54.088
Please, come on.

47:55.698 --> 47:56.830
Come on.

47:58.092 --> 48:00.138
Come on, we need to
turn back, please.

48:00.181 --> 48:01.530
Come on.
I can't leave you here!

48:01.574 --> 48:03.619
[Betriek grunts]
-Come on.

48:06.927 --> 48:08.363
-[Betriek laughs]
-Just stop, please.

48:08.407 --> 48:10.278
-Ah, ah!

48:15.066 --> 48:16.371
-You think it's funny?

48:19.244 --> 48:20.288
-Yes.

48:21.420 --> 48:23.988
[♪♪]

49:00.981 --> 49:04.028
[heavy rainfall]

49:04.071 --> 49:05.333
[Sonja]
Jonas!

49:09.033 --> 49:11.296
[cracking thunder]

49:13.037 --> 49:15.822
Where have you been?
I've been trying to reach you.

49:15.865 --> 49:17.041
[Jonas]
Let's get inside.

49:17.084 --> 49:18.651
[Sonja]
It's not going to work.

49:27.355 --> 49:29.967
[machine whirring]

49:46.331 --> 49:47.723
-Her throat has been cut.

49:47.767 --> 49:49.856
-Yes. Just like the others.

49:52.685 --> 49:53.773
-There are more?

49:53.816 --> 49:55.949
[machine whirring]

49:55.993 --> 49:58.604
[Sonja]
Four, to be precise.

49:58.647 --> 49:59.735
All women.

50:01.346 --> 50:03.087
-That's amazing.
-[chuckles]

50:08.353 --> 50:11.704
-Their throats have
all been cut vertically?

50:11.747 --> 50:13.488
[Sonja]
As far as we can tell.

50:13.532 --> 50:17.144
-These were found in the new
holes, the ones that Radu dug.

50:17.188 --> 50:19.016
-You're kidding me.

50:20.800 --> 50:23.368
[♪♪]

50:32.072 --> 50:35.293
-Wait with the press statement
until we find out more, yeah?

50:35.336 --> 50:37.904
-Sure.
-And, Sonja...

50:40.298 --> 50:43.170
...could you look
something up for me?

50:43.214 --> 50:46.086
[suspenseful music]

50:53.093 --> 50:56.053
[ominous music]

50:56.096 --> 50:58.620
[camera shutter clicks]

50:58.664 --> 51:01.232
[Betriek coughs]

51:06.498 --> 51:09.240
[water dripping]

51:24.429 --> 51:27.301
[floor creaking]

51:34.700 --> 51:37.790
[mysterious music]

51:40.662 --> 51:43.709
[suspenseful music]

51:46.799 --> 51:49.889
[♪♪]

51:56.156 --> 51:57.549
[gasps]

52:03.381 --> 52:05.383
-Ja.

52:17.221 --> 52:20.093
[♪♪]

52:31.931 --> 52:32.932
[Hans]
Wat?

53:37.170 --> 53:38.476
-Uh?

53:45.004 --> 53:48.964
[♪♪]

53:52.098 --> 53:55.232
[♪♪]

53:57.538 --> 54:00.541
[lively chatter]

54:12.727 --> 54:14.294
[woman speaking indistinctly]

54:15.339 --> 54:18.167
[♪♪]

54:22.520 --> 54:24.870
[lively chatter]

54:26.437 --> 54:29.135
[♪♪]

54:33.139 --> 54:36.273
[children singing]

54:59.121 --> 55:02.473
-Here it is.
The legend of Feike.

55:04.170 --> 55:07.434
Many centuries ago,
there was an evil lord, Walter,

55:07.478 --> 55:09.349
and his bitter wife, Helen,

55:09.393 --> 55:13.048
who treated their people poorly
and lived in tremendous wealth

55:13.092 --> 55:16.182
whilst others
were left to struggle.

55:16.878 --> 55:18.750
Together, they commanded
a household

55:18.793 --> 55:21.230
with dozens of servants.

55:21.274 --> 55:24.059
One of them was a young girl
called Feike.

55:25.583 --> 55:28.237
[applause]

55:41.207 --> 55:44.297
[♪♪]

55:48.954 --> 55:51.565
[Sonja] It wasn't long before
Walter started developing

55:51.609 --> 55:53.480
lustful feelings for the girl.

55:57.484 --> 55:59.791
Eventually, the worst happened.

56:00.792 --> 56:02.576
Feike got pregnant.

56:03.882 --> 56:06.972
[♪♪]

56:21.203 --> 56:23.292
[child screams]

56:23.336 --> 56:25.033
[Sonja]
When Helen found out,

56:25.077 --> 56:27.079
there was no shelter
from her fury.

56:28.210 --> 56:30.430
"It wasn't him!" she screamed.

56:30.474 --> 56:34.739
"He was under a spell,
taken over by her heathen mind."

56:36.915 --> 56:39.961
And so Feike was named
a sorceress.

56:41.093 --> 56:42.964
A witch.

56:43.008 --> 56:45.271
Awaiting her fate
in the dungeon,

56:45.314 --> 56:47.142
she prayed to God for help.

56:47.186 --> 56:48.883
-[Feike chanting prayers]

56:48.927 --> 56:51.538
[Sonja] But it was
a different god who listened,

56:51.582 --> 56:54.411
a heathen god, Moloch.

56:55.368 --> 56:58.937
The god of child sacrifice.

56:58.980 --> 57:02.419
"I will help you escape a fate
unworthy of a soul

57:02.462 --> 57:05.334
so beautiful, my child,"
the god whispered.

57:06.292 --> 57:10.122
"But beware, this vengeance
will become a cage of its own

57:10.165 --> 57:13.560
and I will claim what's mine --

57:13.604 --> 57:17.477
your offspring,
even those yet unborn."

57:19.305 --> 57:22.003
And thus, a deal was made
and sealed

57:22.047 --> 57:26.747
with the mark of Moloch burned
into the girl's forehead.

57:27.748 --> 57:32.144
The next day,
Feike stood at the stake.

57:32.187 --> 57:35.495
"Repent!"
the mistress shrieked.

57:35.539 --> 57:38.280
"Confess your guilt
and repent," she insisted.

57:38.324 --> 57:40.805
"Repent!" she repeated
for the third time.

57:42.154 --> 57:45.244
[♪♪]

57:51.511 --> 57:54.949
But Feike courageously
answered, "No.

57:54.993 --> 57:57.604
It is you who shall repent."

57:57.648 --> 58:00.868
She freed her hand, and before
anyone could act...

58:00.912 --> 58:02.566
[audience gasps]

58:02.609 --> 58:04.611
[Sonja]
...she cut her own throat.

58:11.183 --> 58:14.316
As Feike's last breath
left her body,

58:14.360 --> 58:17.406
Helen's wretched soul
was evicted from hers.

58:22.411 --> 58:24.370
From that moment on,

58:24.413 --> 58:29.201
Helen's living and breathing
flesh would belong to Feike.

58:31.029 --> 58:32.465
As the lord's wife,

58:32.509 --> 58:36.164
she exercised her influence
over his rulings.

58:36.208 --> 58:39.994
Before long, happiness
and prosperity had returned.

58:40.038 --> 58:42.344
To this day,
Feike is celebrated

58:42.388 --> 58:44.738
as a true heroine
and a beacon of light.

58:48.481 --> 58:50.352
-She cut her own throat?

58:51.310 --> 58:52.790
-Yes.

58:52.833 --> 58:53.878
-Vertically.

58:53.921 --> 58:56.837
-Um, it doesn't say.

59:15.595 --> 59:18.642
[suspenseful music]

59:24.691 --> 59:27.781
[muted chatter]

59:50.804 --> 59:53.894
[♪♪]

1:00:19.790 --> 1:00:21.574
-[grunts]

1:00:32.541 --> 1:00:36.023
[crow cawing]

1:00:43.465 --> 1:00:46.468
[hammering]

1:00:52.126 --> 1:00:53.737
-[grunts]

1:00:58.002 --> 1:00:59.656
-[Hanna cries]

1:01:02.267 --> 1:01:05.052
-[Hanna cries]
-[phone vibrates]

1:01:06.010 --> 1:01:07.707
-Hallo?

1:01:07.751 --> 1:01:09.491
-Yeah. Hi.
It's...It's Jonas.

1:01:09.535 --> 1:01:10.797
[Betriek]
Hi.

1:01:10.841 --> 1:01:12.712
-Hi.

1:01:14.018 --> 1:01:16.194
I was wondering,
am I gonna see you

1:01:16.237 --> 1:01:18.152
at the Feike party tonight?

1:01:18.196 --> 1:01:21.416
-Yeah, uh...
I'll be there a bit later.

1:01:21.460 --> 1:01:22.722
Around 8.

1:01:22.766 --> 1:01:24.898
I can't come right now.

1:01:25.377 --> 1:01:27.509
There's something I have to do.

1:01:31.078 --> 1:01:34.299
[water bubbling]

1:03:06.957 --> 1:03:09.786
[water bubbling]

1:03:35.072 --> 1:03:37.161
[clears throat]

1:03:45.996 --> 1:03:49.086
[tapping]

1:04:05.929 --> 1:04:08.888
[tense music]

1:04:08.932 --> 1:04:12.022
[tapping continues]

1:04:24.686 --> 1:04:27.646
[tapping continues, echoing]

1:04:27.689 --> 1:04:30.779
[pulsating music]

1:04:32.042 --> 1:04:34.783
[liquid gushing]

1:04:48.493 --> 1:04:49.581
[soft clatter]

1:04:49.624 --> 1:04:52.714
[rhythmic pounding]

1:05:05.684 --> 1:05:07.729
[loud pounding]

1:05:07.773 --> 1:05:08.905
[metal clangs]

1:05:08.948 --> 1:05:10.558
[pounding continues]

1:05:10.602 --> 1:05:11.733
[tense music]

1:05:11.777 --> 1:05:14.867
[screeching]

1:05:17.696 --> 1:05:20.786
[music intensifies]

1:05:29.534 --> 1:05:32.624
[♪♪]

1:05:34.974 --> 1:05:38.021
[choral music]

1:05:45.463 --> 1:05:48.553
[choral music continues]

1:05:59.259 --> 1:06:02.393
[tense music]

1:06:07.137 --> 1:06:08.094
-[Betriek gasps]

1:06:08.138 --> 1:06:11.228
[panting]

1:06:14.318 --> 1:06:17.408
-[Ton moaning]

1:06:27.679 --> 1:06:29.986
[ominous music]

1:06:32.510 --> 1:06:34.164
[car door closes]

1:06:34.207 --> 1:06:36.557
[♪♪]

1:06:45.653 --> 1:06:48.134
-[Betriek sighs deeply]

1:06:48.178 --> 1:06:50.484
[rustling]

1:06:55.881 --> 1:06:57.752
[keypad clacking]

1:07:01.365 --> 1:07:03.497
-[speaking Danish]

1:07:05.978 --> 1:07:10.069
-Hey, I, uh...
could you call me back?

1:07:16.249 --> 1:07:17.337
[car engine revving]

1:07:18.469 --> 1:07:21.559
[dramatic music]

1:07:32.744 --> 1:07:35.790
[dramatic music continues]

1:07:59.118 --> 1:08:00.380
[rustling]

1:08:03.035 --> 1:08:04.080
[Sonja]
Where is she?

1:08:06.169 --> 1:08:07.648
[flap rustles]

1:08:11.957 --> 1:08:15.047
[approaching footsteps]

1:08:35.372 --> 1:08:36.895
[chair clatters]

1:08:39.767 --> 1:08:41.073
[Sonja]
Hey.

1:08:43.554 --> 1:08:45.860
[speaking Dutch]

1:09:09.232 --> 1:09:11.712
[Lennard]
He went to the party, I think.

1:09:46.530 --> 1:09:49.185
[ominous music]

1:09:55.147 --> 1:09:56.757
[twigs cracking]

1:10:12.251 --> 1:10:14.906
[loud tinkling]

1:10:21.652 --> 1:10:24.045
[tinkling]

1:10:24.959 --> 1:10:28.049
[eerie whispering]

1:10:33.620 --> 1:10:36.710
[approaching footsteps]

1:10:40.018 --> 1:10:40.975
[silenced gunshot]

1:10:41.019 --> 1:10:42.673
-[man groaning]

1:10:43.848 --> 1:10:45.023
[thud]

1:10:45.066 --> 1:10:48.156
[tense music]

1:10:57.340 --> 1:10:58.471
[metal clinks]

1:11:04.564 --> 1:11:06.653
[zip ties rustle]

1:11:09.134 --> 1:11:10.527
[tinkling]

1:11:11.441 --> 1:11:14.531
[eerie whispering]

1:11:16.794 --> 1:11:18.317
[echoing whispers]

1:11:23.366 --> 1:11:24.323
[door hinges squeak]

1:11:24.367 --> 1:11:26.760
[Elske] Hey.

1:12:17.855 --> 1:12:18.943
[zipper buzzes]

1:12:22.120 --> 1:12:23.904
[receding footsteps]

1:12:25.689 --> 1:12:28.779
[phone vibrating]

1:12:31.564 --> 1:12:33.523
[dramatic music]

1:12:33.566 --> 1:12:35.176
[fireworks explode]

1:12:35.220 --> 1:12:38.266
[indistinct chatter]

1:12:46.144 --> 1:12:48.015
[crowd shouting]

1:12:54.457 --> 1:12:56.154
[Sonja]
Jonas!

1:12:56.197 --> 1:12:57.460
Jonas!

1:12:58.635 --> 1:13:01.768
[♪♪]

1:13:12.910 --> 1:13:14.433
[tinkling]

1:13:14.477 --> 1:13:15.956
[distant howling]

1:13:24.269 --> 1:13:26.445
[distant howling]

1:13:35.628 --> 1:13:36.716
[tinkling]

1:13:36.760 --> 1:13:39.806
[suspenseful music]

1:13:49.599 --> 1:13:51.339
[howling]

1:13:53.472 --> 1:13:54.560
[tinkling]

1:13:57.476 --> 1:13:58.434
[tinkling]

1:13:58.477 --> 1:14:00.479
[music intensifies]

1:14:01.654 --> 1:14:04.744
[suspenseful music]

1:14:06.485 --> 1:14:09.445
[music intensifies]

1:14:09.488 --> 1:14:11.534
[tinkling]

1:14:17.627 --> 1:14:19.846
-[Roelof breathing heavily]

1:14:22.632 --> 1:14:25.678
[tinkling continues]

1:14:40.867 --> 1:14:43.957
[suspenseful music]

1:14:46.525 --> 1:14:48.527
[tinkling]

1:14:51.487 --> 1:14:53.750
[music intensifies]

1:14:57.754 --> 1:15:00.844
[dramatic music]

1:15:15.772 --> 1:15:18.818
[Roelof sobbing]

1:15:18.862 --> 1:15:21.952
[eerie whispering]

1:15:23.954 --> 1:15:27.044
[whispers intensifying]

1:15:32.484 --> 1:15:35.008
[Jonas] What else did she say?
[Sonja] I don't know.

1:15:35.052 --> 1:15:37.620
She seemed really distraught
about the situation.

1:15:37.663 --> 1:15:42.320
She's really lucky
she didn't damage anything.

1:15:42.363 --> 1:15:44.670
I-I was extremely nice to her,
mind you.

1:15:44.714 --> 1:15:46.019
-She's been through a lot.

1:15:46.063 --> 1:15:47.717
-Yeah, I know,
with the attack and all.

1:15:47.760 --> 1:15:49.588
-It's not just that.

1:15:49.632 --> 1:15:53.287
Her husband died,
grandmother was murdered,

1:15:53.331 --> 1:15:56.943
and now the old--
-Her grandmother was murdered?

1:15:56.987 --> 1:15:59.816
-Yeah. Uh...
-You're not gonna tell me

1:15:59.859 --> 1:16:03.515
somebody slit her throat,
are you?

1:16:03.559 --> 1:16:05.386
-Why would you say that?

1:16:05.430 --> 1:16:07.650
-Holy shit. Did someone--
-I don't know.

1:16:09.434 --> 1:16:11.131
-[woman laughing]

1:16:16.441 --> 1:16:17.877
-Do you think
it's still happening?

1:16:19.792 --> 1:16:21.098
-What?

1:16:23.753 --> 1:16:25.145
-The sacrifices.

1:16:27.757 --> 1:16:31.108
