1:28:26.344 --> 1:28:27.345
[door opens]

1:28:31.828 --> 1:28:33.090
[door closes]

1:28:37.703 --> 1:28:39.879
-Thank you for meeting me here.

1:28:40.967 --> 1:28:44.319
I'm only in Holland for a day,
so...

1:28:44.362 --> 1:28:45.450
Yeah, it's been crazy.

1:28:47.060 --> 1:28:48.584
-It's nice.

1:28:48.627 --> 1:28:50.716
-Yeah?
-What is it?

1:28:51.761 --> 1:28:53.980
-It's the guesthouse.

1:28:54.024 --> 1:28:55.721
Yeah, it came with the place,
so...

1:28:55.765 --> 1:28:57.767
But it's not--
it's not getting much use.

1:28:58.507 --> 1:29:00.422
-It's nice.

1:29:00.465 --> 1:29:02.467
-If you want, you and Hanna

1:29:02.511 --> 1:29:04.904
are more than welcome
to come and stay.

1:29:04.948 --> 1:29:07.385
I can imagine the both of you
could use some time

1:29:07.429 --> 1:29:10.432
away from here,
change of scenery.

1:29:10.475 --> 1:29:12.695
You could bring your violin.

1:29:12.738 --> 1:29:17.177
Uh...maybe record
an album or two.

1:29:17.221 --> 1:29:18.309
Thank you.

1:29:18.353 --> 1:29:19.615
-No. I sold it.

1:29:21.834 --> 1:29:23.488
-You sold it?

1:29:23.532 --> 1:29:24.881
-Yeah.

1:29:27.405 --> 1:29:31.366
I think it's best to have
some stability now, you know?

1:29:31.409 --> 1:29:33.672
Stick to the familiar
with Hanna.

1:29:33.716 --> 1:29:36.327
-Yeah, yeah.
Of course. I understand.

1:29:39.809 --> 1:29:41.550
How is she doing?

1:29:41.593 --> 1:29:43.682
[Betriek]
She's plowing through.

1:29:43.726 --> 1:29:47.382
-Glad to see that both of you
are coping so well.

1:29:47.425 --> 1:29:48.818
-Yeah.

1:29:48.861 --> 1:29:50.254
-Yeah.

1:29:50.297 --> 1:29:54.345
You probably should talk
to someone as well.

1:29:54.389 --> 1:29:56.086
I mean, professional.

1:29:56.129 --> 1:30:01.221
-Well, I have my mantra,
and it seems to work.

1:30:03.223 --> 1:30:05.095
[chuckles]
I don't know how to translate.

1:30:05.138 --> 1:30:07.227
It's, uh, something like...

1:30:08.185 --> 1:30:09.752
..."Just keep going."

1:30:12.581 --> 1:30:15.497
-[laughs] Yeah.

1:30:15.540 --> 1:30:16.889
Blik op oneindig.

1:30:16.933 --> 1:30:19.283
-Well, it sounds like
a good mantra.

1:30:19.326 --> 1:30:20.893
-Yeah, works for me.

1:30:23.243 --> 1:30:24.462
What's yours?

1:30:25.637 --> 1:30:27.247
-Uh, I don't know.

1:30:30.207 --> 1:30:33.819
I'm having trouble focusing
lately, if I'm being honest.

1:30:33.863 --> 1:30:35.560
-Oh.
-Yeah.

1:30:35.604 --> 1:30:41.261
Tomorrow they have scheduled
a lecture for me in Paris, so...

1:30:41.305 --> 1:30:43.525
I'm in trouble.
Yeah.

1:30:45.352 --> 1:30:46.832
-Well, I'm sure you'll be fine.

1:30:50.009 --> 1:30:51.054
-Yeah.

1:30:55.841 --> 1:30:58.148
-So...
-So...

1:30:58.191 --> 1:31:00.716
-Well, it was really nice
seeing you again.

1:31:00.759 --> 1:31:01.847
Hanna!

1:31:01.891 --> 1:31:03.022
-Okay.

1:31:04.459 --> 1:31:05.547
Yeah.

1:31:08.680 --> 1:31:10.726
If you reconsider,
please call me, huh?

1:31:12.467 --> 1:31:14.817
I think it would be good
for the both of you.

1:31:14.860 --> 1:31:17.297
In fact, I would really enjoy
the company.

1:31:18.516 --> 1:31:20.344
-Okay.

1:31:21.258 --> 1:31:23.042
Stop worrying.

1:31:23.086 --> 1:31:24.348
Yeah?

1:31:26.742 --> 1:31:28.352
You look tired.

1:31:29.396 --> 1:31:31.007
Take care of yourself.

1:31:31.050 --> 1:31:32.225
-Okay.

1:31:34.619 --> 1:31:35.838
-We'll be fine.

1:31:38.493 --> 1:31:43.019
With these things,
sometimes it's best to just...

1:31:43.062 --> 1:31:44.499
leave it be.

1:31:47.066 --> 1:31:48.677
There's your mantra.

1:31:48.720 --> 1:31:50.330
-Leave it be.

1:31:51.723 --> 1:31:53.551
-Yeah.

1:31:53.595 --> 1:31:55.901
[tense music]

1:31:58.251 --> 1:31:59.905
Leave it be.

1:32:00.906 --> 1:32:02.255
Hanna.

1:32:03.169 --> 1:32:04.431
-Oh!

1:32:13.615 --> 1:32:14.616
